eur in search of the meaning of the modern game. He captures the magnificence and mastery of today’s most accomplished NBA players while paying homage to the devotion of countless congregants in the global church of pickup basketball. He shares his own stories from the courts, meditating on basketball’s role in city life and its impact on the athlete’s psyche as he moves from youth to middle age. Part journalistic account, part memoir of a slightly talented player whose main gift is being tall, Lost in the Game charts the game’s inexorable gravitational hold on those who love it.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 0aBasketball players. 0aBasketball. 7aSPORTS & RECREATION / Basketball.2bisacsh  aurban sketch.40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781478023449?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781478023449423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781478023449/original  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles